{"id": 5474, "title": "Ticket #5474: Stack should delete its corresponding S3 bucket (if created).", "description": "<blockquote>\nTell the stack, when it's created, if we (condor_annex) created the S3 bucket it will be downloading things from.  If we did, delete that bucket when the stack is deleted.\n\n<p>An empty bucket can't be deleted, and we only delete files we know about, so won't cause data loss.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Jan-14 12:35</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/af7322b33e3afca8653b45c0d9e5fb1279ad5218\">[47456]</a></span>: (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5474\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5474'); return false;\" title=\"Stack should delete its corresponding S3 bucket (if created).\">#5474</a></span>, <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5475\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5475'); return false;\" title=\"Allow user to add to annex nodes' configuration\">#5475</a></span>) Delete created buckets on stack deletion. Allow user to specify a file to be uploaded and become part of the annex nodes' config dir.  (By Todd L Miller )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "experimental", "last_change": "2016-Jan-14 14:37", "status": "resolved", "created": "2016-Jan-12 16:19", "fixed_version": "2016-Jan-12 16:19", "broken_version": "", "priority": "4", "subsystem": "", "assigned_to": "tlmiller", "derived_from": "#5324", "creator": "tlmiller", "rust": "", "customer_group": "other", "visibility": "public", "no